      • getApplication

        default ProjectModel getApplication()
        Returns the application that this file is a part of. This is especially useful in the case of analyzing multiple application's, as we often need to know which application a particular file is associated with.

        This is a shortcut for calling getProjectModel().getRootProjectModel().

        Note: In the case of a shared library, this may return the "shared-libs" application.

      • getApplications

        default List<ProjectModel> getApplications()
        Gets the list of all applications that this file is a part of. This will include both the "shared-libs" project as well as any actual applications.
        Specified by:
        getApplications in interface HasApplications
        Returns:
        root project models

      • retrieveSize

        default Long retrieveSize()
        Returns the size of the file, if it is an existing file. Otherwise return null. It's not necessary to store file size on all FileModels. Some submodels have it as a property.
